				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">re:  Churizo
<br />

<br />
1.  You've not been unreasonable on the pet heal issue.  It's not an issue I have with *people who play beastlords* just the fact that SoE has not taken action on the problem.  My point was that many people use the 'they're part shaman' excuse to try to justify the current mage vs bst pet heal situation; which when looked at in the same picture as high level shaman heals is pure bunk.  I agree with you on the issue of mage vs bst pet heals.  Beastlords *should* get the better pet heals in terms of raw #s.  However, the excuse that the greater heal amount of Sorsha is justified because it is pet only is also bunk--if it is being compared to shaman heals directly.  The logic works in terms of numerics and usefulness; just not as an explanation of the heal's power when trying to relate it to shaman spells.
<br />

<br />
2.  I can burn down a mob quickly, but when am I going to do this burning down while I'm chainhealing my pet to keep him alive?  I could chain a RS, but any time I do that there is a chance that I'll lag or interrupt or something and die.  Slowed mobs are much safer.  Mages must sustain themselves and their pet as well.  This is a 65% more difficult task for mages, so why are our heals so inneffective?  Probably also a gear issue for my weak 2khp ass.
<br />

<br />
3.  Well... I'm not happy with it.  Sure mage pets get a mitigation bonus, but beastlords get their mitigation AAs, as well as 65% slow.  How do I equal that?
<br />

<br />
Pet class it is then.  Agree that pets are not scaled with content.  The contradiction I intended to point out was that, while a beastlord's pet is a damage dealer; it is not the only means of damage migitation/prevention that a beastlord has.  At the high end, beastlord warders are a DoT when soloing, not something that is all that stands between the player and death.
<br />

<br />
I'll retry kiting in PoV... Last time I tried my pet generated too much aggro and got mashed.  
<br />

<br />
As for AAs, a BST friend of mine was bragging about how easily he was soloing BoT for insane xp.  (With 66+ spells)  If this hasn't been your experience, I would appreciate a bit of info on the topic.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Dorai Darkspire, 65 Arch Convoker of Maelin Starpyre
